Nils Oudejans’s Experience

  • Director Wholesale

    ACN

    (Privately Held; 201-500 employees; Telecommunications industry)

    February 2007 — Present (1 year 8 months)

    Responsible for all European wholesale activities for ACN. ACN used to be non-facility based. All services sold to ACN customers in 15 European countries must be bought in-country with local telecom-players. These wholesale activities concern the fixed CPS and WLR product, as well as DSL and VoIP services, as well as Mobile services. Because of the country and product portfolio I have a real pan-European view on the wholesale market.

    ACN now will also invest in an European VoIP Network to enable the launch of VideoPhones! Therefore partners in all European countries are searched.

  • Manager Carrier Relations

    ACN

    (Privately Held; 201-500 employees; Telecommunications industry)

    April 2001 — January 2007 (5 years 10 months)

    A very diverse role that overtime developed as ACN grew into 15 European countries. Main responsibilities over the years:
    o Commercial relation with most CPS carriers and DSL providers.
    o All operational escalation for 15 European countries.

    Business development achievements:
    o Carrier selection for CPS services in: Austria, Ireland, Italy, France, Switzerland, Belgium, Spain, Portugal and Poland.
    o Carrier Selection for WLR service in: Denmark, UK, France and the Netherlands.
    o Provider Selection for ESP (mobile services) in: Finland (and started them in Germany and the Netherlands).
    o Provider selection for DSL services in Switzerland and Germany.

    Knowledgeable in operational issues like customer-activation-process and billing. In the first years also responsible for the product proposition in the Nordic region.

  • Director Stream Management

    KPN INS

    (Public Company; 10,001 or more employees; KPN; Telecommunications industry)

    April 2000 — March 2001 (1 year)

    Responsible for the purchasing and routing for all international traffic generated within KPN terminated to both fixed and mobile networks as well as the purchasing, routing and pricing for international wholesale minutes.

  • Senior Stream Manager

    KPN INS

    (Public Company; Telecommunications industry)

    March 1999 — March 2000 (1 year 1 month)

    Responsible for the purchasing and routing for traffic to most important European destinations and Asia, as well as the purchasing, routing and pricing for traffic towards these destinations.

  • Manager Distribution Development & Control

    KPN Inkoop en Logistiek

    (Public Company; 10,001 or more employees; Telecommunications industry)

    January 1998 — February 1999 (1 year 2 months)

    Responsible for transforming a paper oriented warehouse into a fully equipped data warehouse system organized environment. The warehouse of KPN at that time had 30.000 different products and 9.000 pick orders per day. In total 150 people worked hard to get this daily job done.

  • Planner Plus

    KPN Inkoop en Logistiek

    (Public Company; 10,001 or more employees; Telecommunications industry)

    April 1996 — December 1997 (1 year 9 months)

    Optimizing the service stock on both:
    (i) The service cars that field engineers take with them the solve outages on location
    (ii) The central service stock that can grow because of repaired units or new units.

  • Expeditiemanager

    KPN Telecom Repair

    (Public Company; 10,001 or more employees; Telecommunications industry)
